other_tests.findings: Small bilateral pleural effusions with associated compressive lower lobe atelectasis; a segment 3 hypointense T1 nonenhancing lesion is likely a cyst biliary hamartoma; gallbladder is markedly distended with multiple small gallstones, thickening of gallbladder wall, mural edema, and pericholecystic stranding; suspicious of gangrenous cholecystitis.
NO POLYMORPHONUCLEAR LEUKOCYTES SEEN. NO MICROORGANISMS SEEN.
